ters to you, from anywhere! Completely wire-free cameras fit anywhere - and can be viewed from your smartphone, PC, or Mac. </span><span class="c1 c12">Netgear</span><span class="c15 c1 c13">]</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;. Vuezone had a FMS based system &ldquo;built-in&rdquo; which needed complex layers of rendering to move the FPS from 5 to 24/27 Standards. Using BackBone and Angular JS allowed for the development approach that could interface with a RESTful Java Server Module via Node JS. In doing this, JavaScript-based Video playback was achieved using Doxygen </span><span class="c1 c46"><a class="c28" href="http://www.ffmpeg.org/doxygen/0.6/classes.html">FF MPEG for C</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;and </span><span class="c1 c49"><a class="c28" href="http://jquerymobile.com/resources/">JQuery UI Mobile</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;for frame rendering at real-time. An essential percentage of this project was finished by our development team of 3 and facilitated a scalable approach for Android and iOS platforms - while encapsulating a JavaScript UI that stabilized as &ldquo;its own platform&rdquo; for Cross-Platform and Cross-Device implementation and Software Deployment.<br></span></p><p class="c6"><span class="c1"><br><br><br></span><span class="c3 c1">Senior UI/Flex Developer<br></span><span class="c2 c20 c1">Lender Processing Services, Inc. (LPS)</span></p><p class="c6"><span class="c29 c20 c34">November 2011</span><span class="c29 c20 c34">&nbsp;&ndash; February 2013 </span><span class="c11">(1 years 10 months) </span><span class="c29 c20 c34"><br>Riverside, CA | San Diego, CA | Oklahoma City, OK</span></p><p class="c6"><span class="c1">reInsight </span><span class="c22"><a class="c28" href="http://www.lpsvcs.com/MLS/Pages/default.aspx">[link]</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Use/Role: MLS Mapping UI: Business Rules: Application Development: Developed Several components with properties that needed practical layout conventions when new or refreshed data